// eslint-disable-next-line no-alert alert(&#34;foo&#34;); alert(&#34;foo&#34;); // eslint-disable-line no-alert It&rsquo;s also possible to omit the name of the rule, and in this case lint is turned off for that specific line.

You have a custom directive, repeatHelloWorld; it has the important task to log the message &ldquo;Hello, world!&rdquo; in the console, the number of times specified by the parameter accepted by the directive, and defined in the controller.
